main event: A civilian observed a single unidentified object in the sky over Hickory, North Carolina on 10/1/68.
interesting points: The object was observed for approximately 30 minutes,The object appeared bluish-white or reddish-orange in color,It seemed to give off its own light rather than reflecting light,Other witnesses reported seeing similar objects in the area,The conclusion was labeled as insufficient data because the observer was likely seeing Venus.
